1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,588
Many teams begin by choosing a framework, drawing a multi-agent diagram, and asking several models to debate.

2
00:00:06,538 --> 00:00:12,057
Anthropic found that successful production systems often use simpler, composable patterns.

3
00:00:12,057 --> 00:00:19,413
Quality depends less on the number of agents than on clear task boundaries, evaluation criteria, and environmental feedback.

4
00:00:19,413 --> 00:00:26,480
A complex architecture may not improve completion, but it will increase model calls, latency, cost, and debugging.

5
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:31,442
Every extra handoff adds another chance to lose context or pass a mistake forward.

6
00:00:31,442 --> 00:00:42,711
In this video, we will answer three questions that are easy to get wrong: when one model call is enough, which of five common workflow patterns fits the task, and when an autonomous agent is actually worth the risk.

7
00:00:42,711 --> 00:00:51,557
By the end, you will have an Agent Architecture Decision Ladder that you can use on a real project, instead of paying for complexity just to make the system look more agentic.
